'''EDP Dobrogea Wind Farm''' is a large wind power project in the [[Northern Dobruja|Dobrogea region]], [[Romania]].  It will consist of 113 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>[http://www.standard.ro/articol_66924_12/edp_face_un_parc_eolian_de_225_mw_in_circa_doi_ani.html EDP face un parc eolian de 225 MW in circa doi ani {{ro}}]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> each with a [[Intermittent power source#Terminology|nameplate capacity]] of around 2 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]].  Collective output will be up to 226 MW of power, enough to power over 148,030 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$300 million.

