)<sub>2</sub> |- | {{chem|BN|3|6−}} || trigonal planar ||145–149<ref name = "Meyer Inorg Chem Focus3"/><ref name="BlaschkowskiJing2002"/>|| ||[[borate|{{chem|BO|3|3−}}]], [[carbonate ion|{{chem|CO|3|2−}}]]||La<sub>6</sub>(BN<sub>3</sub>)O<sub>6</sub> |- | {{chem|B|2|N|4|8−}} || planar ||147–150<ref name = "Meyer Inorg Chem Focus3"/>||177–182<ref name = "Meyer Inorg Chem Focus3"/> ||[[oxalate ion|{{chem|C|2|O|4|2−}}]]||La<sub>3</sub>B<sub>2</sub>N<sub>4</sub>, ((La<sup>3+</sup>)<sub>3</sub>({{chem|B|2|N|4|8−}})(e<sup>−</sup>)) |- | {{chem|B|3|N|6|9−}} || planar or chair form ||144–151<ref name = "Meyer Inorg Chem Focus3"/>|| ||||La<sub>3</sub>B<sub>3</sub>N<sub>6</sub><ref name="ReckewegMeyer1999">{{cite journal|last1=Reckeweg|first1=Olaf|last2=Meyer|first2=H.-Jürgen|title=Lanthanoidnitridoborate mit sechsgliedrigen B<sub>3</sub>N<sub>6</sub>-Ringen: Ln<sub>3</sub>B<sub>3</sub>N<sub>6</sub>|journal=Angewandte Chemie|volume=111|issue=11|year=1999|pages=1714–1716|issn=0044-8249|doi=10.1002/(SICI)1521-3757(19990601)111:11<1714::AID-ANGE1714>3.0.CO;2-X}}</ref> |}
