{{Infobox scientist |name = Dr. Paul Chun |image = |image_size = 150px |birth_date = |birth_place = |nationality = [[United States]] |field = [[Biochemistry]] |work_institutions = [[University of Florida]] |alma_mater = [[University of Missouri]] |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = Knowledge of thermodynamics |prizes = }}
'''Paul W. Chun''' is a [[professor emeritus]] at the [[University of Florida]]. He is a researcher in the field of protein folding equilibria,<ref name="energetics_of_biological_macromolecules_a01">{{Cite book | last1 = Johnson | first1 = Michael R. | last2 = Ackers | first2 = Gary K. | title = Energetics of biological macromolecules | year = 1995 | publisher = Academic Press | location = San Diego | isbn = 978-0-12-182196-8 | pages = }}</ref> in particular, he is known as the "leading proponent" of using the Planck-Benzinger thermal work function to understand protein folding thermodynamics and stability. As such Chun has written a number of papers relating to the [[thermodynamics]] of protein folding.<ref>[http://biochem.med.ufl.edu/facultytemp.php?lastname=Chun&firstname=Paul+W. Faculty profile at the University of Florida] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071022063634/http://biochem.med.ufl.edu/facultytemp.php?lastname=Chun&firstname=Paul+W. |date=2007-10-22 }}.</ref> He received his Ph.D. in 1965 from the [[University of Missouri]] for work on the interaction of [[casein]] [[molecule]]s, and joined the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology at the University of Florida soon thereafter.<ref name="handbook_of_biochemical_kinetics">{{Cite book | last1 = Purich | first1 = Daniel L. | last2 = Allison | first2 = R. Donald | title = Handbook of biochemical kinetics | year = 2000 | publisher = Academic Press | location = San Diego, CA | isbn = 0-12-568048-1 | pages = }}</ref> He retired in 2003.<ref>[http://www.news.health.ufl.edu/news/story.aspx?ID=759 Paul Chun, Ph.D. , professor of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology retires]{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, University of Florida Health News, July 7, 2003. Retrieved 2009-10-27.</ref>
He has published 68 [[peer-review]]ed papers listed in [[Scopus]].
