A '''planing mill''' is a facility that takes cut and seasoned boards from a [[sawmill]] and turns them into finished dimensional [[lumber]].<ref name=Britannica>{{cite web |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/663493/planing-mill |title= Planing mill |publisher= [[Encyclopædia Britannica|Britannica Online]] |accessdate= 2011-01-07}}</ref> Machines used in the mill include the planer and matcher, the molding machines, and varieties of saws.<ref name=Britannica/> In the planing mill planer operators use machines that smooth and cut the wood for many different uses.<ref name=Career>{{cite book |title= Career Information Center |chapter= Lumber Mill Worker Job Description |edition= 9th |date= January 1, 2007 |publisher= Visual Education Corporation}}</ref>
