{{Politics of Slovenia}}
A '''referendum on building a coal-fired power plant''' was held in [[Slovenia]] on 10 January 1999.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & Stöver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1778 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of the construction of the TET3 coal-fired power plant. The proposal was rejected by 79.8% of voters, although voter turnout was just 27.3%.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p1785</ref>
